BofA Names Murphy, Schleusner Co-Heads of Leveraged Finance

-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   I d z e l i s
-- 
2011-08-31T20:56:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-31/bank-of-america-names-murphy-schleusner-as-co-heads-of-leveraged-finance.html
Bank of America Corp. (BAC) , the largest
underwriter of U.S. leveraged loans this year, named A.J. Murphy
and Robert Schleusner as co-heads of global leveraged finance,
according to an internal memo.  Murphy and Schleusner will replace David Flannery, who was
named risk management executive for global banking and markets.  Kerrie McHugh, a spokeswoman for the  Charlotte , North
Carolina-based lender, confirmed the contents of the memo.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christine Idzelis in New York at 
 cidzelis@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
